definitions.definition: The act of traveling; passage from place to place.
examples: I like travel , but it’s always too tiring.
I’m off on my travels around France again.
He released his travels in 1900, two years after returning from Africa.

definitions.definition: The activity or traffic along a route or through a given point.
The working motion of a piece of machinery; the length of a mechanical stroke.
examples: There was a lot of travel in the handle, because the tool was out of adjustment.
My drill press has a travel of only 1.5 inches.

definitions.definition: Distance that a keyboard's key moves vertically when depressed.

main_definition: The act of traveling; passage from place to place.
secondary_definitions: ( in the plural ) A series of journeys .
( in the plural ) An account of one's travels.
